The paper deals with constructing error-correcting codes for permutations and multi-permutations, which are combinatorial objects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). However, the paper also mentions applications in rank modulation for flash memories, which involves coding theory and information theory. Hence, it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves partitioning sets and constructing codes with less redundancy symbols, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper mentions applications in flash memories, which could also fall under cs.SI (Systems and Control).
